commit.message:
Replacing the pre rewards nothing with B loop

- This file had tabs, let's keep them

Instead of diligently doing nothing, we bash B repeatedly

- Optimize the reward waiting time
- ~15 seconds intermission on strike (safe could be as low as 5 seconds)
- ~4.5 seconds intermission on non-strike (cutting it close)
- Performance: ~12000 rupees/hour

Do not split, but throw again

- Second throw is not optimised, it just throws
- Additional reward waiting had to be added which adds padding to the normal strike flow
- Current rupees generation rate: ~11500 rupees/hour

Revert the throw back to the previous one

- On Teensy 2.0 (atmega32u4), the previous throw is showing better success rate.
- Modifications also to walking back instructions on failed throw

Tuning on timing, and a fix on double variable declaration (#14)

* First cleanup, without function changes

* Fixed the printing offset issue

It was mainly due to RX and RY sticks set to zero in the report (also with a physical joycon you get the same bounce back arounf the edges).

I had to revert the printing direction to avoid a pixel skipping issue (also this one was present with a physical joycon).

I cleaned up printing states, adding one to syncronize the starting position.

Finally, I replaced the "braking" concept with an "echo" one, cheking the time with a spin loop. This seems more robust to skipping pixels issues (IMHO mainly coming from the Switch being busy in processing something else).

* Updates on the printing procedure

* Tuning on timing, and a fix on double variable declaration

With 40 ms of echo wait time you may still see some pixel skipping, expecially when printing lines with some white or black continous areas (not a big issue for dithered images, but still something worth to fix). Is a bit slower :-(.

image_data declared as external (as it should formally be), to improve compiler compatibility.

* Missing newline at the EOF
Update converters to accept an -i parameter, which will generate an inverted colormap (#12)

Updates on the printing procedure (#11)

* First cleanup, without function changes

* Fixed the printing offset issue

It was mainly due to RX and RY sticks set to zero in the report (also with a physical joycon you get the same bounce back arounf the edges).

I had to revert the printing direction to avoid a pixel skipping issue (also this one was present with a physical joycon).

I cleaned up printing states, adding one to syncronize the starting position.

Finally, I replaced the "braking" concept with an "echo" one, cheking the time with a spin loop. This seems more robust to skipping pixels issues (IMHO mainly coming from the Switch being busy in processing something else).

* Updates on the printing procedure
